I had some problems a little while ago using dateCompare() and the same thing bit me recently with dateDiff(). Well really I had a problem with createODBCDate(), but let me explain.
I wanted to compare the &ldquo;day&rdquo; value between 2 dates like;
&lt;cfscript&gt; date1 = now(); date2 = myQuery.dateCreated; dateDifference = dateDiff(&quot;d&quot;, date1, date2);	&lt;/cfscript&gt;  The initial problem was that &ldquo;myQuery.dateCreated&rdquo; has a time value associated with it, as does the value of now().

Have you ever pasted code you are working on to a colleague over IM or even email for some help or an opinion? Then you would benefit from using pastebin (free service) particularly if you experienced problems with code over IM in the past :(
&ldquo;Pastebin is a tool for collaborative debugging or editing&rdquo;
What that means is you can paste any code into a nice big textarea on the pastebin homepage, choose your syntax highlighting (ColdFusion is available!

